    <example>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Use the  Inland postal charges to work
          out the following questions bellow.
        </p>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                In which mass limits do we find letters with the following masses:
              </p>
              <p>
                a) <m>45\,g \,\text{?}   \qquad \text{b)} 155\,g\,\text{?}</m>
              </p>
              <p>
                c) <m>500\,g \,\text{?}   \qquad \text{d)} 1.9\,kg\,\text{?}</m>
              </p>

            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Cherotich sent four weighing <m>120\,g\, ,\,40\,g\, ,\,250\,g\, \text{and} \,1\,kg</m>. How did 
                he play altogether?
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                How much does it cost to send <m>2</m> single postcards?
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          From the table, it clearly shows how mass limits is generated.
        </p>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                a) A letter weighing <m>45\, g</m> is found in a mass limit of 
                <m> {\color{green} \text{over} \, 20\,g\, \text{up to} \, 250\,g}</m>.
              </p>
              <p>
                b) A letter weighing <m>155\, g</m> is found in a mass limit of 
                <m> {\color{green} \text{over} \, 100\,g \,\text{up to} \, 250\,g}</m>.
              </p>
              <p>
                c) A letter weighing <m>500\, g</m> is found in a mass limit of 
                <m> {\color{green} \text{over} \, 250\,g \,\text{up to} \, 500\,g}</m>.
              </p>
              <p>
                d) A letter weighing <m>1.9\, g</m> is found in a mass limit of 
                <m> {\color{green} \text{over} \, 1\,kg \,\text{up to} \, 2\,kg}</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <md>
                  <mrow> \text{A letter weighing } \,120\,g=\amp sh\,46 </mrow>
                  <mrow> \text{A letter weighing } \,40\,g=\amp sh\,30</mrow>
                  <mrow> \text{A letter weighing } \,250\,g=\amp sh\,46</mrow>
                  <mrow> \text{A letter weighing } \,1\,kg=\amp sh\,114</mrow>
                  
                </md>
              </p>
              <p>
                <m>sh \,46+\,sh \,30+\,sh \,46 \,sh \,114={\color{blue} sh \,236}</m>
              </p>

            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>1 </m> postcard cost <m>= \, sh\,15</m>
              </p>
              <p>
