          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  a) <m>sh\, 4\,500</m> is in the range <m>sh\, 1\,000\,-\,4\,999</m>. It earns an iterest of <m>2\%</m> per year.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Interest} =\amp 2\% \, \text{of} \, sh\, 4\,500</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{2}{100} \times sh\, 4\,500  </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp  {\color{blue} sh\,90}</mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                  b) <m>sh\, 16\,000</m> is in the range <m>sh\, 15\,000\,-\,19\,999</m>. It earns an iterest of <m>5\%</m> per year.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Interest} =\amp 5\% \, \text{of} \, sh\, 16\,000</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{5}{100} \times sh\, 16\,000  </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp  {\color{blue} sh\,800}</mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Interest} =\amp 5\% \text{of} \, sh\, 17\,500 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{5}{100} \times sh\, 17\,500 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp {\color{green} sh\, 875} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{Total amount of money} =\amp \text{Money deposited} + \text{Interest} </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp sh\, 17\,500+ {\color{green} sh\, 875} </mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp {\color{blue} sh\, 18\,375} </mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
              </li>


            </ol>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
